<h2><span id="Why_containers?"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Why_containers.3F">Why containers?</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.02/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.02/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-1" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="cdferwp201801 image3.png" src="/mediawiki/images/thumb/3/36/cdferwp201801_image3.png/900px-cdferwp201801_image3.png" width="900" height="368" srcset="/mediawiki/images/thumb/3/36/cdferwp201801_image3.png/1350px-cdferwp201801_image3.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/3/36/cdferwp201801_image3.png 2x" data-file-width="1764" data-file-height="722"></a>
</p><p>The application landscape is changing, let’s list 4 main areas:
</p>
<ul><li>Architecture: “glued” applications to loosely coupled services</li>
<li>Process: slow changes to continuous updates</li>
<li>Technology: human to machine operated</li>
<li>Sourcing: single delivery to a hybrid delivery model</li></ul>
<p>The adoption of containers is driven by the transformation of applications, desire for higher productivity and agility and a SaaS like experience requirement.
</p><p>Write once run anywhere is an enticing proposition for any software developer and opens up new ways of delivering software with SaaS-like experience.
</p>
<h2><span id="What_drives_container_adoption?"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="What_drives_container_adoption.3F">What drives container adoption?</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.02/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-2" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.02/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-2" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="cdferwp201801 image4.png" src="/mediawiki/images/thumb/7/7f/cdferwp201801_image4.png/900px-cdferwp201801_image4.png" width="900" height="406" srcset="/mediawiki/images/thumb/7/7f/cdferwp201801_image4.png/1350px-cdferwp201801_image4.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/7/7f/cdferwp201801_image4.png 2x" data-file-width="1736" data-file-height="784"></a>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Standards_and_policies">Standards and policies</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.02/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-3" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.02/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-3" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>In the process of containerizing products, Micro Focus is defining usage standards in the following areas: container OS, images and engines, repositories and delivery.
</p><p>Container OS Standard
</p><p><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="cdferwp201801 image5.png" src="/mediawiki/images/thumb/8/83/cdferwp201801_image5.png/900px-cdferwp201801_image5.png" width="900" height="314" srcset="/mediawiki/images/thumb/8/83/cdferwp201801_image5.png/1350px-cdferwp201801_image5.png 1.5x, /mediawiki/images/thumb/8/83/cdferwp201801_image5.png/1800px-cdferwp201801_image5.png 2x" data-file-width="1980" data-file-height="690"></a>
</p><p>openSUSE is our container OS base layer due to its relatively small size, support by a commercial entity, alignment with our host OS strategy.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Docker_and_Engines_Standard">Docker and Engines Standard</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.02/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-4" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.02/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-4" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>A consistent set of best practices for how to build a lean and quality container image have been defined along with support policy for Docker engine versions, both open source and Enterprise Edition.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Docker_Container_Repository_Standard">Docker Container Repository Standard</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.02/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-5" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.02/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-5" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>All container images are stored in Docker Hub for internal and external usages as primary repository.
</p><p>A local cache Registry2 is configured.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Docker_Store_Delivery_Standard">Docker Store Delivery Standard</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.02/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-6" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.02/WhitepaperContainerStandardsPolicy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-6" title="Edit section: ">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<p>For software products that are delivered through the new Docker Store, a set of standards and best practices outline how to prepare for container publishing in aspects such as vulnerability scanning and cleaning, image structure best practices etc.
</p>
